OL,3,CWolverhampton Wanderers appoint Rob
OL,4,CEdwards as their new head coach
OL,6,FBorn in Telford, Edwards' affinity
OL,7,Fwith Wolves first began in 2004. He
OL,8,Fplayed 111 times across four seasons
OL,9,Fwith the club, most notably in the
OL,10,Fcentre of defence under Mick McCarthy.
OL,12,FEdwards, who was capped 15 times by
OL,13,FWales, later enjoyed spells with
OL,14,FBlackpool ` where he won promotion to
OL,15,Fthe Premier League as a player ` and
OL,16,FBarnsley, and made his first steps
OL,17,Finto coaching with Wolves' under-18s
OL,18,Fin 2014.
